node.text: Let’s be real… postpartum is hard! It’s just part of the journey. My initial recovery & my experience of birth was a challenge for sure and it’s taken time for me to overcome anxious thoughts and memories from the birth of Honey that planted that initial root, “is my baby okay?” I actually just shared all about this on my podcast this week! Every little noise she made made me panic and worry if she was okay! I'm so thankful that I've had people to talk to and relate to about this. That was a huge step in getting to a better place! I've found the @peanut app to be a really safe space to share experiences and worries with other moms. Speaking to other women on the app who can relate  can help you realize that all of our thoughts and feelings are totally normal and you’re not alone. I’m so thankful for the people who have reassured me that “this is normal” in a time that didn’t feel very normal ❤️ It's so important to have a strong community when you're trying for a baby, pregnant or a new mom. If you’re feeling a little afraid - you are not alone! We all need a community to walk through seasons with so I encourage you to join @peanut! #peanutapp

node.text:
Honey J is 2 months old today 💛
We loved getting to share our birth story this week with all of you! Thank you so much for the positive response. It was amazing to relive all the miracles as we told the story. 

So many of you asked about my worship playlist that I had playing during labor and asked about the other ways that I had prepared. 
I actually just made my own playlist during the time I was pregnant with her. I would be worshiping in my car and hear a song I would want to pray over Honey or I felt peace in or strengthened by and I would just add it to the album. I will link my album in my story, but I honestly encourage anyone going into labor or in their own particular season to create their own album because of how personal the words became.🤍 
I also created a shared notes album with christian where I added scriptures to speak out, declarations and meditation from the @glorifyappofficial to play, and even some funny things for a good laugh 😂 that all came in great handy! 

I have always loved the verse in Joshua when it talks about being strong and courageous. However, it has always kind of intimidated me because sometimes it’s hard to be strong and courageous. One day I realized that right before God commands Joshua to be strong and courageous, He tells Him to not let the book of the law depart from His mouth and to mediate on the word. 
I realized finally that the two go hand in hand. When you mediate on the word of God and the power of the word then you realize you don’t have much to fear and it makes you strong and courageous. All of the sudden the magnitude of who God is makes fear look very tiny. 
So for those or you who are going into something that might scare you I encourage you to cling to THE WORD and worship your way through. 💗

“Out of the mouth of babies and infants, you have established strength” - Psalms 8:2
